				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ding 63! Ding AA 12! Ding FM!<a name="32557"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 2 04 2:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One point of INT is 13 mana.  That means a +6 augment is 78 mana.  That means it would take a dozen of them to pay for one fade.  Now, if you are in adventures and get the chance to loot an INT augment, by all means loot it!  You can always dissolve it out if you need to.  But don't spend AP on an INT or Mana augment until you've bought all the FT augments you can use.  A +10 INT augment costs 357 AP.  You can buy a FT1 augment (if you have a type 3 slot for it) for 340.
<br />

<br />
The bottom line is you want all three -- Flowing Thought, Intelligence stat boosters, and raw mana boosters.  Until you get FT 10 or so, FT will mean more than raw INT.  Until you get your INT close to max, raw INT will generally mean more than raw mana.  But you want all 3.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
