				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ding 63! Ding AA 12! Ding FM!<a name="32586"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 2 04 4:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First off grats!
<br />

<br />
Second, I'll echo what Steppy said in that it really is a balance (not only between ft, int, and mana, but also with HP/AC/resists/etc.).
<br />

<br />
From your magelo I notice you have FT1 and 2270 mana.  With a KEI (and time to med to full mana) you will have enough mana for 3 fades.  Given your low FT, I think MC1 is a very good deal.  I would also suggest going after the eye of the owlbear mother (drops from named owlbear during hollowshade moor war and has very crappy stats but is FT1).  You could easily solo it.  I think that you also gain an extra point of standing mana regen at level 65 (for a total of 3/tick).  Those three things would cut your med time between fades from 30 min to 15 min. (My math assumes a standing regen of 2 mana/tick at level 63).  Once you are down to a regen time of 10-12 mins per fade then mana pool size begins to play a larger role as you will start to use fade more regularly instead of just in &quot;oh crap!&quot; situations.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
