				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ding 63! Ding AA 12! Ding FM!<a name="32614"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 2 04 8:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When you're pullng for a raid, five fades is great. I wish I could get more, but it's hard to imagine. I have FT6 (all from augments) and when I get under 50% I swap in my soltice earing and composer boots for some extra juice.  
<br />

<br />
Saying that you're doing something wrong if you need to fade five times in a row is silly. If if at some point you need to burn 2 or 3 fades on one pull, you still have to keep pulling. And that extra buffer has a great meaning. Without it, you have to call in a monk, a replacement bard or risk an unneccesary death.  In the course of the raid, I will get mana back on easier pulls, but running out is the pits.
<br />

<br />
Some mobs are just hard to split and you have to split them. Also you might still be in range of a see invis mob on the first fade. It will cause him to stop a bit, but then he resumes the chase. You can use his momentary pause to give you the distance for a second fade to work.
<br />

<br />
BTW, I don't belive that Song of Dawn takes you off rampage. Rampage is chronolgical. Fade wipes you off all hate lists. 
<br />

<br />
Also... one int = 13 mana? At what level? Isn't it INT &lt;200  ten per and at INT 200+ it's six. 250+ is a lot less.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
