			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Ding 63! Ding AA 12! Ding FM!<a name="32635"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 2 04 11:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Saying that you're doing something wrong if you need to fade five times in a row is silly.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I would have to agree with this completely.  It would be like saying that a monk that has to fd multiple times in order to make an especially hard pull is doing something wrong.  Fading Memories is a tool.  The more able one is to use it, the more one is going to use it.  Toss in EQ's &quot;always a chance to fail&quot; law and it would be quite possible to burn a ton of fades, given the circumstances.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Some mobs are just hard to split and you have to split them. Also you might still be in range of a see invis mob on the first fade.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
The same thing can apply to timing.  In a bad situation you could fade with a bunch of mobs trying to hand you your head on a platter right before a server tick.  The mobs will pause, but then you get proximity agro on the server tick.  Waiting for the server tick would solve the problem of having to fade twice, but then could very well wind up incurring the downtime needed in order to remed mana due the rez.  The same applies if a caster has already started a spell cast on you.
<br />

<br />
Being able to fade at least twice is essential to really maintain a decent ratio on benefit received.  While you may not need the additional fade in general, it is really nice to have it there on the occassions you do need it.
<br />

<br />
Besides questing for ft items/augs, you can also work on AAs in order to purchase up to MC3, Body and Mind Rejuvination, as well as Innate Int and Improved Innate Int.  Ultimately it will depend on your preference as to how to do it in relationship to your playstyle.
<br />

<br />
Polara Magami
<br />
64 Melodic Disciple</span></td>
